QUALIFICATION: subsequently described as Liparetrus rufescens in Blanchard, C.E. 1850. Muséum d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris. Catalogue de la Collection Entomologique. Classe des insectes. Ordre des Coléoptères. Paris : Museum d'Histoire Naturelle Vol. IV 128 pp. (112) where he quotes pl. 8, fig. 11 (Philochlaenia) (1842), sine descript.; Sherborn, C.D. & Woodward, B.B. 1901. Notes on the dates of publication of the natural history portions of some French voyages.--Part I. 'Amérique méridionale'; 'Indes orientales': 'Pôle Sud' ('Astrolabe' and 'Zélée'); 'La Bonite'; 'La Coquille'; and 'L'Uranie et Physicienne'. Annals and Magazine of Natural History 7 7: 388-392 (390) give the publication date of the text as 1853, but do not mention the Atlas containing 25 colour plates; Musgrave, A. 1932. Bibliography of Australian Entomology 1775-1930 with biographical notes on authors and collectors. Sydney : R. Zool. Soc. N.S.W. viii 380 pp. gives the publication date of the text as 1853 and the Atlas as 1842-1853. We here follow the date given on the title page of the Atlas Zoologique, namely 1846
